episodes.title: Episode #1.1
episodes.plot: Agent Malotru returns to Paris after 6 yrs undercover in Damascus and begins training Marina Loiseau, a future undercover agent in Iran. Agent Cyclone goes missing after a DUI arrest in Algeria and the department comes together to find him.

episodes.title: Episode #1.2
episodes.plot: With Cyclone still missing, the Bureau now has to handle the exfiltration of another asset in Algeria.

episodes.title: Episode #1.3
episodes.plot: Malotru decides to test Gherbi's loyalty by luring him into a trap. Nadia joins in on a mysterious meeting with other Syrians, but her "night-outs" arouse the suspicion of a Syrian agent.

episodes.title: Episode #1.4
episodes.plot: At a French-Algerian meeting, Malotru attempts to read the other Algerian officers to find out whether or not they are holding Cyclone in detention.

episodes.title: Episode #1.5
episodes.plot: When Sisteron goes after Cyclone in Algiers, another agent known as Pigalle reaches out to Malotru with potential Intel about Cyclone.

episodes.title: Episode #1.6
episodes.plot: While attempting to trade Pigalle's Intel on Cyclone, Malotru must find a way to uncover the former's true identity and underlying motive.

episodes.title: Episode #1.7
episodes.plot: Kerbouche is finally brought to the DGSE and unveils the truth about Cyclone's life-or-death situation, which requires immediate action from the Bureau.

episodes.title: Episode #1.8
episodes.plot: Devastated by Malotru's revelations, Nadia cannot set out to betray her country and refuses to join the DGSE.

episodes.title: Episode #1.9
episodes.plot: Encouraged by the French government, the DGSE pretends to accept a deal offered by the Algerian DG. But on the side, Mag secretly asks Malotru for a plan B to avoid any foreign interference.

episodes.title: Episode #1.10
episodes.plot: At the DGSE, Sisteron is anxiously waiting for Cyclone's release over the next few days. Malotru takes a few days off the Cyclone operation and secretly meets up with the CIA.
